d 'TOHTML': module to convert Stata log files to HTML reports
d
d     tohtml is specifically designed to work hand-in-hand with
d ishere, forming a unified    workflow embodied by the phrase:
d everything is here: from do to html. This design    philosophy
d emphasizes a minimalist approach to reproducible research—where
d "is here"    corresponds to the ishere command (marking where
d elements belong), and "to html"    corresponds to the tohtml
d command (converting marked logs into polished reports).    The
d core principle is simple: everything you need for your analysis
d lives in one	  place—your do-file.  You mark locations with
d ishere, run your analysis, and tohtml    transforms the log into
d a professional HTML report. No external tools, no manual editing,
d    no copy-pasting—just a streamlined path from code to
d publication-ready output.    tohtml converts Stata log files
d containing ishere markers into formatted HTML reports.    The
d command can process a single log file or a directory containing
d multiple table and	figure files. The latter gathers all table
d and figure files in the directory in a HTML. 
d
d KW: data management
d
d Requires: Stata version 17 and pathutil from SSC (q.v.)
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260427
d
